+- src/sync.py:14 Using floor division for the page count drops every remainder page and returns no users at all when `total_count` is below `PAGE_SIZE`.
+- src/sync.py:24 The mutable `seen` default persists IDs across calls, causing later independent sync operations to silently skip users synced by earlier calls.
+- src/sync.py:35 Interpolating staged email and ID values directly into SQL permits SQL injection and also makes ordinary emails containing apostrophes fail to sync.
+- src/report.py:5 Returning early for an empty user list leaves the opened report file descriptor unclosed.
+- src/report.py:11 Calling `lower()` and indexing the result of `split("@")` crashes report generation for schema-valid NULL emails or addresses without an `@`.
